imageDescriptions.description: HERO SHOT of Alexander (8-12, medium brown tousled hair, green eyes, casual hoodie) standing in a dim, damp mill interior, a majestic silver-antlered stag (Silberhorn der Hirsch) upright beside him wearing patched leather boots and a burlap sack. LIGHTING: soft, muted golden hour light leaking through slatted windows, dust motes visible. FOREGROUND: scattered flour sacks and a coiled leather strap. MIDGROUND: Alexander and Silberhorn in quiet agreement, Alexander’s small hands gripping a homemade boot. BACKGROUND: silent waterwheel and shadowed brothers with a donkey. MOOD: surprised hopefulness, humble resilience. Watercolor illustration style, Axel Scheffler inspired, warm-cool contrast, gentle textures.

WIDE SHOT of a steam-filled market street. Alexander (green-eyed, tousled brown hair, hoodie) and Silberhorn der Hirsch (majestic stag with silver antlers, leather boots) present small clockwork wonders to Busfahrer Bernd (52, warm expression, blue uniform) near a brass steam-bus. LIGHTING: morning steam diffused golden light, soft highlights on metal. FOREGROUND: curious townsfolk and a small mechanical bee glowing blue. MIDGROUND: Adrian (7-9, ginger curls, bright sky-blue eyes) leaning forward, skeptical. BACKGROUND: shopfronts and chimneys, faint gears turning. MOOD: playful intrigue, clever showmanship. Watercolor illustration style, Axel Scheffler inspired, lively textures and warm hues.

DRAMATIC ANGLE of a steam-driven carriage halting beside a wide copper-lined canal. LIGHTING: dramatic steampunk sunset backlight, steam halos. FOREGROUND: frantic townsfolk and a soaked Alexander (tousled brown hair, green eyes) being helped onto the bank. MIDGROUND: Silberhorn der Hirsch (silver antlers, leather boots) calling loudly, making a theatrical plea. Gärtnerin Rosa (40, gardener) leaning forward, concerned, soil on knees. BACKGROUND: Adrian (ginger curls, bright blue eyes) watching, thoughtful and skeptical. MOOD: tense, theatrical, slightly comic. Watercolor illustration style, Axel Scheffler inspired, warm-brass palette and textured brushwork.

CLOSE-UP of Silberhorn der Hirsch (majestic stag with silver antlers, brown fur, bright expressive eyes) in a wheat field, telling a tale. LIGHTING: late afternoon golden hour, warm rim light on fur. FOREGROUND: waving wheat stalks blurred, the hush of breeze. MIDGROUND: Silberhorn speaking, an intense, conflicted expression. BACKGROUND: Alexander in a simple hoodie in a cart, looking uneasy; distant figures of farmers nodding reluctantly. MOOD: reflective, conflicted, tender. Watercolor illustration style, Axel Scheffler inspired, textured strokes, warm earth tones and soft shadows.

imageDescriptions.chapterTitle: Die Stunde von Adrian und Alexander
imageDescriptions.description: HERO SHOT inside a clockwork manor. LIGHTING: warm interior lamp glow with dramatic shadows from brass cogs. FOREGROUND: Alexander (tousled brown hair, green eyes) working intensely on a small clock mechanism. MIDGROUND: Adrian (short curly ginger hair, bright sky-blue eyes) watching with a half-smile, hands tucked into his jacket. Silberhorn der Hirsch stands tall behind them, thoughtful. BACKGROUND: mechanical birds on perches, Busfahrer Bernd and Gärtnerin Rosa near a table with blueprints. MOOD: inventive, reconciliatory, hopeful. Watercolor illustration style, Axel Scheffler inspired, rich textures and warm-cool contrasts.
